cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD, cs.SE

The paper presents an online tool condition monitoring approach based on an ensemble learning algorithm with an active learning scenario and ensemble merging scenario. This involves machine learning techniques such as online learning, active learning, and ensemble learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also involves artificial intelligence techniques such as feature selection and concept drift detection, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of neural networks and decision trees in the algorithm also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves real-world manufacturing data streams, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as well.
